The paper deals with countably infinite Markov decision processes (MDPs) and their optimal strategies for parity objectives. This topic falls under the area of logic (cs.LO) as well as discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of memory in strategies, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper provides a complete picture of the memory requirements for optimal strategies, which is related to game theory (cs.GT).
